ros-humble-benchmark-framework (0.1.7) UNRELEASED; urgency=low

  * Add --csv-out flag to analyze_trigger_latency.py: writes a flat CSV with
    one row per node/input→output pair. Columns: session, node, pipeline_stage,
    input, output, n, mean_ms, stdev_ms, min_ms, p50_ms, p90_ms, p99_ms,
    max_ms, trigger_count, fps, jitter_mean_ms, jitter_max_ms.
  * Add --csv-out flag to analyze_pipeline_latency.py: writes a flat CSV with
    one e2e summary row and one row per pipeline stage. Columns: type, session,
    stage, representative_node, representative_input, representative_output,
    mean_ms, p50_ms, p90_ms, p99_ms, max_ms, n, throughput_hz, drop_rate_pct,
    bottleneck_stage, cpu_mean_pct, cpu_max_pct.
  * Add --xlsx-out flag to both scripts: writes the same columns as --csv-out
    to an Excel workbook with bold headers and auto-width columns.
    Requires openpyxl (pip install openpyxl); gracefully skips if not installed.
  * Add CSV/Excel export usage examples to CHEATSHEET.txt.
  * Add tests/test_csv_export.py: smoke tests for --csv-out flag presence
    and end-to-end Level 2 CSV generation using a synthetic kpi.json fixture;
    no ROS install required.
  * Add unit-tests job to .github/workflows/build-test-scan.yml running
    tests/test_csv_export.py on every push/PR to main.

